  "note": [
    {
      "text": "Discovered on examination (irregularly irregular pulse) and confirmed by in-office 12-lead ECG. Ventricular rate 92 bpm. Symptoms of palpitations and exertional dyspnea over 6-8 weeks consistent with atrial fibrillation. Patient hemodynamically stable. Workup initiated with TTE, TSH, CBC, CMP."
    },
    {
      "authorReference": {
        "reference": "Practitioner/5a20a547-c65e-4778-ada0-094d81a05ea3",
        "display": "Dr. Angela Whitfield, MD"
      },
      "time": "2026-01-26",
      "text": "Workup complete: ECG confirms AF rate 92, TTE shows preserved EF 58% with mild LA dilation 4.3 cm, no significant valvular disease, labs normal (TSH 2.1, CBC unremarkable, CMP normal), no reversible cause identified. CHA2DS2-VASc score 1 (hypertension). Treatment initiated: metoprolol succinate 50 mg daily for rate control, apixaban 5 mg BID for stroke prevention. Referred to cardiac electrophysiology for catheter ablation evaluation."
    }
